'We're looking for safe place... What he got was a bullet in his heart.' 

Earlier this week, authorities released surveillance footage showing the four young men walking from the complex at the time of the shooting. 

No words were exchanged before the gunfire broke out.

Salem explained in an account on Facebook that Al-Jumaili had taken cover behind a pickup truck when the men opened fire - but a bullet pierced the truck and struck him.

Al-Jumaili was shot in the chest and ran towards the nearest building, where he collapsed.

He was rushed to hospital, where he passed away the following day. 

'There was nothing said to Ahmed or his wife and her brother by the perpetrators in advance of the shots,' Salem wrote. 'Including no verbal insults or derogatory slurs.' 

A LaunchGood fundraising page explains Al-Jumaili and Zahara married just 16 months ago, and planned to move to the U.S., seeking refuge from the Islamic State. 

