The neighborhood where Al-Jumaili was killed has a large immigration population and northern Dallas is home to a large number of Iraqi refugees. 

The fundraiser has raised more than $30,000 toward Al-Jumaili's memorial and family fund.

North Texas Crime Stoppers offered a reward of $5,000 for information leading to an arrest or indictment.

Salem said the Council on American-Islamic Relations raised an additional $7,000 reward for information to help in the investigation into the killing.

